title: 6 people shot, including teenager, in Prince George's Co.
content:
PRINCE GEORGE'S CO., MD. (WUSA9) - Six people were shot, including a teenager, in Prince George's County early Sunday morning.
Police say 2 people are dead, 1 person is critically injured and 3 people are in serious condition after being shot in the 6800 block of Walker Mill Road.
The victims have not been identified at this time.
Detectives working to identify suspect(s) and motive. Please call 1-866-411-TIPS with any information. There is up to $25,000 reward available.
This is a developing story and will be updated.
